def plot_words_en(stopwords, text, type='wordcloud', title=None):
    """
    Parameters
        ----------
        stopwords : set
            stopwords set.
            
        text : string
            text to be processed.
            
        type : wordcloud or wordcount, default='wordcloud'
            If type equals to 'wordcloud', plot the word cloud.
            If type equals to 'wordcount', plot the word count with bar graph.
        title: int, 0 or 1 => 0: All Comments 1: Negative Comments
            
    Returns
        -------
        None.

    """
    if type == None or type == 'wordcloud': # plot wordcloud
        wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 1600, height = 1000, stopwords = stopwords, background_color = 'white').generate(str(text))
        plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8), facecolor = None)
        plt.imshow(wordcloud)
        plt.axis('off')
        plt.tight_layout(pad = 0)
        if title==0:
            plt.title('Most Common Words in All Comments', fontsize=20)
        if title ==1:
            plt.title('Most Common Words in Negative Comments', fontsize=20)
        plt.show()
    elif type == 'wordcount':
        wordcount = WordCloud(width = 1000, height = 1000, stopwords = stopwords, background_color = 'white').process_text(str(text))
        wc_df = pd.DataFrame(data = wordcount.values(), index=wordcount.keys())
        wc_df = wc_df.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False)
        
        wc_df.iloc[:20,].plot(kind = 'bar', figsize = (9, 9), fontsize = 22, legend = False)
        if title==0:
            plt.title('Most Common Words in All Comments', fontsize=20)
        if title ==1:
            plt.title('Most Common Words in Negative Comments', fontsize=20)
    else:
        sys.stderr.write('Error: argument "type" only includes wordcloud, wordcount: ')
        sys.exit(1)

def topic_model(df):
    # Creating the vectorizer object
    tf_vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df=0.9, min_df=25, max_features=5000)

    # apply the transformation to create the document term matrix
    tf = tf_vectorizer.fit_transform(df['lemmatized_comments'].values.astype('U'))
    tf_feature_names = tf_vectorizer.get_feature_names()
    doc_term_matrix = pd.DataFrame(tf.toarray(), columns=list(tf_feature_names))
    lda_model = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=10, learning_method='online', max_iter=500, random_state=0).fit(tf)
    no_top_words = 10

    def display_topics(model, feature_names, no_top_words):
        for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(model.components_):
            print("Topic %d:" % (topic_idx))
            print(" ".join([feature_names[i]
                              for i in topic.argsort()[:-no_top_words - 1:-1]]))

    print(display_topics(lda_model, tf_feature_names, no_top_words))
    return (lda_model, tf, df)
